{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mayotte", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Mayotte, France}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mayotte\n| map1            = File:Mayotte communes map-fr.png\n| places          = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Mayotte]]\n| first_case      = \n| arrival_date    = 13 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=13|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[France]]\n| confirmed_cases = 339<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation/339-cas-confirmes-au-total-Coronavirus-COVID-19|title=339 cas confirm\u00e9s au total Coronavirus COVID-19|access-date=23 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> (2020-04-23)\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 125\n| deaths          = 4\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation COVID-19]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the French [[overseas department and region]] of [[Mayotte]] on 10 March 2020. On 31 March the first person died of Covid-19.<ref name=\"first_death\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=wmd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Mayotte\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar|apr}}\n</div>\n\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-03-13;  0;   0;   1;;;   1;\n;            0;   0;   1;;;   1;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-17;  0;   0;   2;;;   3;+200%\n2020-03-18;  0;   0;   3;;;   3;=\n2020-03-19;  0;   0;   4;;;   4;+33%\n2020-03-20;  0;   0;   6;;;   6;+50#\n2020-03-21;  0;   0;   9;;;   9;+50#\n2020-03-22;  0;   0;  11;;;  11;+22%\n2020-03-23;  0;   0;  21;;;  21;+91%\n2020-03-24;  0;   0;  30;;;  30;+43%\n2020-03-25;  0;   0;  35;;;  35;+17%\n2020-03-26;  0;   0;  42;;;  42;+20%\n2020-03-27;  0;   4;  50;;;  50;+19%\n2020-03-28;  0;   7;  63;;;  63;+26%\n2020-03-29;  0;   8;  74;;;  74;+17%\n2020-03-30;  0;  10;  82;;;  82;+11%\n2020-03-31;  1;  10;  94;;;  94;+15%\n2020-04-01;  1;  10; 101;;; 101;+7.4%\n2020-04-02;  2;  10; 116;;; 116;+15%\n2020-04-03;  2;  13; 128;;; 128;+10%\n2020-04-04;  2;  14; 134;;; 134;+4.7%\n2020-04-05;  2;  14; 147;;; 147;+9.7%\n2020-04-06;  2;  15; 164;;; 164;+6.8%\n2020-04-07;  2;  22; 171;;; 171;+4.2%\n2020-04-08;  2;  23; 184;;; 184;+7.6%\n2020-04-09;  2;  38; 186;;; 186;+1.0%\n2020-04-10;  2;  50; 191;;; 191;+2.7%\n2020-04-11;  3;  57; 196;;; 196;+2.6%\n2020-04-12;  3;  67; 203;;; 203;+3.6%\n2020-04-13;  3;  69; 207;;; 207;+1.9%\n2020-04-14;  3;  69; 217;;; 217;+4.8%\n2020-04-15;  3;  74; 221;;; 221;+1.8%\n2020-04-16;  3;  94; 233;;; 233;+5.4%\n2020-04-17;  4; 117; 245;;; 245;+5.2%\n2020-04-18;  4; 117; 254;;; 254;+3.6%\n2020-04-19;  4; 117; 271;;; 271;+6.7%\n2020-04-20;  4; 117; 284;;; 284;+4.8%\n2020-04-21;  4; 125; 311;;; 311;+9.5%\n2020-04-22;  4; 125; 326;;; 326;+4.8%\n2020-04-23;  4; 125; 339;;; 339;+4.0%\n|caption=Data sourced from [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation COVID-19]\n14-16 March missing, but assumed no change.\n}} \n===March===\nA man from the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Oise]], [[France]], arrived in [[Mayotte]] on 10 March. He had a suspicious [[flu]], and was observed for three days in a [[hospital]]. After testing him on 13 March, the man tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/mayotte-enregistre-premier-cas-coronavirus-810856.html|title=Mayotte enregistre un premier cas de Coronavirus|first=Toufaili|last=Andjilani|newspaper=[[La Premi\u00e8re (France)|Mayotte 1\u00e8re]]|date=14 March 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, A third case, also a traveler, was identified . The island enters confinement as on French territory. With a single hospital center for a population of 279,000 inhabitants and precarious living conditions (84% live below the poverty line), there is great concern. As in [[R\u00e9union]], the island is also affected by [[dengue fever]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2020/04/07/covid-19-mayotte-se-prepare-a-faire-face-a-la-vague_6035819_823448.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte se pr\u00e9pare \u00e0 \" faire face \u00e0 la vague \"|date=2020-04-07|work=Le Monde.fr|access-date=2020-04-11|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the authorities set up a health control system at [[Dzaoudzi\u2013Pamandzi International Airport|Dzaoudzi airport]], with volunteer school nurses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-point-de-situation-et-conduite-tenir|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : Point de situation et conduite \u00e0 tenir|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, [[French National Assembly]] member [[Mansour Kamardine]] was very concerned and arranged 69 additional hospital beds to be shipped to Mayotte, because there were only 61 [[intensive care|ICU]] beds.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/03/25/coronavirus-les-territoires-ultramarins-alertent-sur-une-possible-catastrophe-sanitaire_6034405_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : \u00e0 la Guadeloupe, en Guyane, \u00e0 la Martinique et \u00e0 Mayotte, la crainte d\u2019une possible catastrophe sanitaire|website=[[Le Monde]]|language=fr|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nA [[curfew]] was instituted between 20:00 and 05:00. Gathering with more than two people are banned. Traffic restrictions apply throughout the island. <ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Restrictions-de-circulation-sur-l-ensemble-du-territoire-COVID-19-Mayotte|title=Restrictions de circulation sur l\u2019ensemble du territoire COVID-19 Mayotte |language=fr|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the bar of 50 cases was reached.\n\nOn 31 March, [[Mayotte]] recorded its first death.<ref name=\"first_death\">{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-covid-19-12-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-mayotte-94-au-total-818100.html |title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : 12 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte : 94 au total |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re |language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n===April===\nOn 1 April, the bar of 100 cases is exceeded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-7-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-mayotte-101-au-total|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : 7 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte : 101 au total|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, MP [[Mansour Kamardine]] was hospitalized and tested positive for Covid-19; it was locally contaminated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-depute-mansour-kamardine-teste-positif-au-covid-19-819526.html|title=Le d\u00e9put\u00e9 Mansour Kamardine test\u00e9 positif au COVID-19|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Meeting Voynet Mutualite 2006-04-05 n2 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Dominique Voynet]]\nOn 8 April, a second death related to Covid-19 is announced ; just as in the first case, the person presented with aggravating pathologies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-184-cas-de-covid-19-confirmes-au-total-a-mayotte-820926.html|title=Coronavirus : 184 cas de COVID-19 confirm\u00e9s au total \u00e0 Mayotte|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> On 16 April, [[Dominique Voynet]], Director of Mayotte Regional Health Agency, announced that the deceased was Said Toihir, the [[Grand Mufti]] of the Comoros.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-grand-mufti-des-comores-est-decede-du-coronavirus-823672.html|title=Le grand Mufti des Comores est d\u00e9c\u00e9d\u00e9 du Coronavirus|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> The announcement caused a diplomatic rift between [[Comoros]] and [[France]]. [[Mohamed El-Amine Souef]], Foreign Minister of Comoros said \"If a case is confirmed in the Comoros, it is not Dominique Voynet to announce it, we have been independent since 6 July 1975.\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/l-union-des-comores-denonce-une-violation-du-secret-medical-et-professionnel-823988.html|title=l'Union des Comores d\u00e9nonce \" Une violation du secret m\u00e9dical et professionnel \"|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, the ARS announced 191 cases, including 41 health professionals; 17 people are hospitalized, including 4 in intensive care; 50 patients are recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-mayotte-191-cas-confirmes-au-total|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 \u00e0 Mayotte : 191 cas confirm\u00e9s au total|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n<br>\nThe report of the Scientific Council on the Evolution of the Coronavirus in the Overseas Territories has been released which calls for strict confinement, doubling of hospital capactity. The situation in Mayotte is considered worrying and therefore calls for an \"extra-hospital\" structure to isolate the asymptomatic cases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/coronavirus-le-conseil-scientifique-craint-une-aggravation-de-la-situation-outre-mer-et-preconise-le-maintien-strict-du-confinement-821800.html|title=Coronavirus: the scientific council fears a worsening of the Overseas situation and recommends \"the strict maintenance of confinement\"|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April, a third death was declared; the number of cases increases slightly to 196.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-mayotte-enregistre-un-3eme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-822004.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte enregistre un 3\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au COVID-19|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April, there are 203 confirmed cases. 67 people have recovered, and more than 1,400 tests have been performed thus far.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-le-cap-des-200-cas-est-franchi-a-mayotte-822244.html |title=Coronavirus : Le cap des 200 cas est franchi \u00e0 Mayotte |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re |language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April, there are 207 confirmed cases including 42 health workers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-covid-19-a-mayotte-207-cas-confirmes-au-total-soit-4-cas-supplementaires-en-24h-822452.html|title=Coronavirus : 207 cas confirm\u00e9s au total, soit 4 cas suppl\u00e9mentaires en 24h. |language=fr|access-date=13 April 2002|website=France TV info}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 April, health care professionals from France have come to the aid of Mayotte. They have all been tested prior to boarding, and will not be quarantined on arrival, but have to abide by special precautionary rules.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-10-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-en-24h-217-au-total-822818.html| title=Coronavirus : 10 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s en 24h, 217 au total| language=fr | access-date=14 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April, a group of students from Mayotte in France, have written open letter that they wished to be repatriated because they have been confined in a near empty [[dormitory]] for almost a month now.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Pour le rapatriement des \u00e9tudiants Mahorais|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/pour-le-rapatriement-des-etudiants-mahorais-823208.html|language=fr | access-date=15 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref> No plans for repatriation from France have been announced yet.\n\nA positive case was discovered from [[Comoros]] where there are officially no Covid-19 infections. As a result, all nautical activities have been banned in order to better guard against illegal border crossings by boat.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/un-cas-de-coronavirus-a-ete-importe-des-comores-823226.html|title=Un cas de Coronavirus a \u00e9t\u00e9 import\u00e9 des Comores|language=fr | access-date=15 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April, measures have been put in place for pregnant women, because up to date 10 tested positive. 1,600 tests have been performed.<ref name=\"upd-04-16\">{{Cite news |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-12-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-a-mayotte-233-au-total-823556.html |title=Coronavirus : 12 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte, 233 au total |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re| language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n<br>\n[[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Colombet]], the [[List of colonial and departmental heads of Mayotte|Prefect]] of Mayotte, said that the current situation is a fight on multiple fronts where food aid is also a major issue. \u20ac2 million in food stamps are being distributed. Colombet also calls upon the food markets to remain open during [[Ramadan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-prefet-de-mayotte-on-y-va-a-fond-823250.html|title=Le pr\u00e9fet de Mayotte : \" on y va \u00e0 fond ! \"|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re| language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, the fourth death was announced. 1,700 tests have been performed up to now.<ref name=\"upd-04-17\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-mayotte-enregistre-un-4eme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-823930.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte enregistre un 4\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au COVID-19|language=fr|access-date=17 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April, it was announced that 108 people had died in March, an increase of 30% compared to 2019. 40% of the deaths are people over 75. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/plus-de-3-morts-par-jour-la-surmortalite-se-confirme-a-mayotte-824348.html|title=Plus de 3 morts par jour : la surmortalit\u00e9 se confirme \u00e0 Mayotte |language=fr |access-date=19 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 April, the Association of Mayotte [[Mayors]] consider that the conditions for reopening of schools are not met, and want more guarantees. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/reouverture-des-ecoles-les-11-mai-l-association-des-maires-de-mayotte-souhaite-avoir-plus-de-garantie-825820.html|title=R\u00e9ouverture des \u00e9coles les 11 mai : l\u2019association des maires de Mayotte souhaite avoir plus de garantie|access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Preventive measures==\n* 15 March 2020 - All schools are closed. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Le-prefet-de-Mayotte-annonce-la-fermeture-des-etablissements-scolaires|title=Coronavirus - COVID19  Le pr\u00e9fet de Mayotte annonce la fermeture des \u00e9tablissements scolaires |access-date=23 April 2020|website=mayotte.gouv.gr|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 15 March 2020 - Social distancing must be observed. All non-essential businesses must close. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Arrete-du-15-mars-2020-portant-diverses-mesures-relatives-de-lutte-contre-la-propagation-du-COVID19|title=Arr\u00eat\u00e9 du 15 mars 2020 portant diverses mesures relatives de lutte contre la propagation du COVID19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 18 March 2020 - People entering Mayotte must self isolate for 14 days. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Un-controle-sanitaire-renforce-a-l-aeroport-de-Dzaoudzi-COVID19|title=Un contr\u00f4le sanitaire renforc\u00e9 \u00e0 l\u2019a\u00e9roport de Dzaoudzi - COVID19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 20 March 2020 - Access to beaches, coves and (uninhabited) islands is prohibited. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Les-plages-criques-et-ilots-de-Mayotte-interdites-d-acces-COVID19|title=Covid19 - Les plages, criques et \u00eelots de Mayotte interdites d\u2019acc\u00e8s |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 25 March 2020 - A [[curfew]] was instituted between 20:00 and 05:00. Gathering with more than two people are banned. Traffic restrictions apply throughout the island. <ref name=\"curfew\"/>\n* 22 April 2020 - Farmers' markets are reopened in [[Coconi]], [[Chirongui]], and [[Kaweni]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Ouverture-de-marches-de-producteurs-a-Coconi-Chirongui-Kaweni-COVID-19|title=Ouverture de march\u00e9s de producteurs \u00e0 Coconi, Chirongui, Kaweni COVID-19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\n==Statistics==\nChronology of the number of active cases\n{{Graph:Chart\n| type = line\n| linewidth = 1\n| showSymbols = 1\n| yType= integer\n| width = 600\n| colors = #ff6347, cyan, black\n| xAxisTitle = Date\n| xAxisAngle = -40\n| xType = date\n| xAxisFormat = %e %b\n| x = 12 March 2020, 13 March 2020, 14 March 2020, 15 March 2020, 16 March 2020, 17 March 2020, 18 March 2020 , 19 March 2020, 20 March 2020, 21 March 2020, 22 March 2020, 23 March 2020, 24 March 2020, 25 March 2020, 26 March 2020, 27 March 2020, 28 March 2020, 29 March 2020, 30 March 2020, 31 March 2020,\n1 April 2020, 2 April 2020, 3 April 2020, 4 April 2020, 5 April 2020, 6 April 2020, 7 April 2020, 8 April 2020, 9 April 2020, 10 April 2020, 11 April 2020, 12 April 2020, 13 April 2020, 14 April 2020, 15 April 2020, 16 April 2020, 17 April 2020, 18 April 2020, 19 April 2020, 20 April 2020, 21 April 2020, 22 April 2020, 23 April 2020\n| yAxisTitle = No. of cases\n| y1 = \n0,     1,   1,   1,   1,   1,   3,   3,   4,   6,   9,  11,  21,  30,  35,  42,  46,  56, 66, 72, 83, <!-- March -->\n90,  104, 113, 118, 131, 147, 147, 159, 146, 139, 136, 133, 135, 145, 144, <!-- -15 April -->\n136, 124, 133, 150, 163, 182, 197, 214\n| yGrid = \n| xGrid = \n}}\nSource: [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation Point de situation at mayotte.gouv.fr]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation Official Site]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in R\u00e9union}}\n{{#related:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Mayotte|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Mayotte]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Overseas France|Mayotte]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Mayotte]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Mayotte, France}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mayotte\n| map1            = File:Mayotte communes map-fr.png\n| places          = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Mayotte]]\n| first_case      = \n| arrival_date    = 13 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=13|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[France]]\n| confirmed_cases = 339<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation/339-cas-confirmes-au-total-Coronavirus-COVID-19|title=339 cas confirm\u00e9s au total Coronavirus COVID-19|access-date=23 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> (2020-04-23)\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 125\n| deaths          = 4\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation COVID-19]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the French [[overseas department and region]] of [[Mayotte]] on 10 March 2020. On 31 March the first person died of Covid-19.<ref name=\"first_death\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=wmd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Mayotte\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar|apr}}\n</div>\n\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-03-13;  0;   0;   1;;;   1;\n;            0;   0;   1;;;   1;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-17;  0;   0;   2;;;   3;+200%\n2020-03-18;  0;   0;   3;;;   3;=\n2020-03-19;  0;   0;   4;;;   4;+33%\n2020-03-20;  0;   0;   6;;;   6;+50#\n2020-03-21;  0;   0;   9;;;   9;+50#\n2020-03-22;  0;   0;  11;;;  11;+22%\n2020-03-23;  0;   0;  21;;;  21;+91%\n2020-03-24;  0;   0;  30;;;  30;+43%\n2020-03-25;  0;   0;  35;;;  35;+17%\n2020-03-26;  0;   0;  42;;;  42;+20%\n2020-03-27;  0;   4;  50;;;  50;+19%\n2020-03-28;  0;   7;  63;;;  63;+26%\n2020-03-29;  0;   8;  74;;;  74;+17%\n2020-03-30;  0;  10;  82;;;  82;+11%\n2020-03-31;  1;  10;  94;;;  94;+15%\n2020-04-01;  1;  10; 101;;; 101;+7.4%\n2020-04-02;  2;  10; 116;;; 116;+15%\n2020-04-03;  2;  13; 128;;; 128;+10%\n2020-04-04;  2;  14; 134;;; 134;+4.7%\n2020-04-05;  2;  14; 147;;; 147;+9.7%\n2020-04-06;  2;  15; 164;;; 164;+6.8%\n2020-04-07;  2;  22; 171;;; 171;+4.2%\n2020-04-08;  2;  23; 184;;; 184;+7.6%\n2020-04-09;  2;  38; 186;;; 186;+1.0%\n2020-04-10;  2;  50; 191;;; 191;+2.7%\n2020-04-11;  3;  57; 196;;; 196;+2.6%\n2020-04-12;  3;  67; 203;;; 203;+3.6%\n2020-04-13;  3;  69; 207;;; 207;+1.9%\n2020-04-14;  3;  69; 217;;; 217;+4.8%\n2020-04-15;  3;  74; 221;;; 221;+1.8%\n2020-04-16;  3;  94; 233;;; 233;+5.4%\n2020-04-17;  4; 117; 245;;; 245;+5.2%\n2020-04-18;  4; 117; 254;;; 254;+3.6%\n2020-04-19;  4; 117; 271;;; 271;+6.7%\n2020-04-20;  4; 117; 284;;; 284;+4.8%\n2020-04-21;  4; 125; 311;;; 311;+9.5%\n2020-04-22;  4; 125; 326;;; 326;+4.8%\n2020-04-22;  4; 125; 339;;; 339;+4.0%\n|caption=Data sourced from [http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Point-de-situation COVID-19]\n14-16 March missing, but assumed no change.\n}} \n===March===\nA man from the [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Oise]], [[France]], arrived in [[Mayotte]] on 10 March. He had a suspicious [[flu]], and was observed for three days in a [[hospital]]. After testing him on 13 March, the man tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/mayotte-enregistre-premier-cas-coronavirus-810856.html|title=Mayotte enregistre un premier cas de Coronavirus|first=Toufaili|last=Andjilani|newspaper=[[La Premi\u00e8re (France)|Mayotte 1\u00e8re]]|date=14 March 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, A third case, also a traveler, was identified . The island enters confinement as on French territory. With a single hospital center for a population of 279,000 inhabitants and precarious living conditions (84% live below the poverty line), there is great concern. As in [[R\u00e9union]], the island is also affected by [[dengue fever]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2020/04/07/covid-19-mayotte-se-prepare-a-faire-face-a-la-vague_6035819_823448.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte se pr\u00e9pare \u00e0 \" faire face \u00e0 la vague \"|date=2020-04-07|work=Le Monde.fr|access-date=2020-04-11|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the authorities set up a health control system at [[Dzaoudzi\u2013Pamandzi International Airport|Dzaoudzi airport]], with volunteer school nurses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-point-de-situation-et-conduite-tenir|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : Point de situation et conduite \u00e0 tenir|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, [[French National Assembly]] member [[Mansour Kamardine]] was very concerned and arranged 69 additional hospital beds to be shipped to Mayotte, because there were only 61 [[intensive care|ICU]] beds.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/03/25/coronavirus-les-territoires-ultramarins-alertent-sur-une-possible-catastrophe-sanitaire_6034405_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : \u00e0 la Guadeloupe, en Guyane, \u00e0 la Martinique et \u00e0 Mayotte, la crainte d\u2019une possible catastrophe sanitaire|website=[[Le Monde]]|language=fr|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nA [[curfew]] was instituted between 20:00 and 05:00. Gathering with more than two people are banned. Traffic restrictions apply throughout the island. <ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Restrictions-de-circulation-sur-l-ensemble-du-territoire-COVID-19-Mayotte|title=Restrictions de circulation sur l\u2019ensemble du territoire COVID-19 Mayotte |language=fr|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the bar of 50 cases was reached.\n\nOn 31 March, [[Mayotte]] recorded its first death.<ref name=\"first_death\">{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-covid-19-12-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-mayotte-94-au-total-818100.html |title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : 12 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte : 94 au total |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re |language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n===April===\nOn 1 April, the bar of 100 cases is exceeded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-7-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-mayotte-101-au-total|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 : 7 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte : 101 au total|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, MP [[Mansour Kamardine]] was hospitalized and tested positive for Covid-19; it was locally contaminated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-depute-mansour-kamardine-teste-positif-au-covid-19-819526.html|title=Le d\u00e9put\u00e9 Mansour Kamardine test\u00e9 positif au COVID-19|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Meeting Voynet Mutualite 2006-04-05 n2 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Dominique Voynet]]\nOn 8 April, a second death related to Covid-19 is announced ; just as in the first case, the person presented with aggravating pathologies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-184-cas-de-covid-19-confirmes-au-total-a-mayotte-820926.html|title=Coronavirus : 184 cas de COVID-19 confirm\u00e9s au total \u00e0 Mayotte|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> On 16 April, [[Dominique Voynet]], Director of Mayotte Regional Health Agency, announced that the deceased was Said Toihir, the [[Grand Mufti]] of the Comoros.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-grand-mufti-des-comores-est-decede-du-coronavirus-823672.html|title=Le grand Mufti des Comores est d\u00e9c\u00e9d\u00e9 du Coronavirus|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> The announcement caused a diplomatic rift between [[Comoros]] and [[France]]. [[Mohamed El-Amine Souef]], Foreign Minister of Comoros said \"If a case is confirmed in the Comoros, it is not Dominique Voynet to announce it, we have been independent since 6 July 1975.\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/l-union-des-comores-denonce-une-violation-du-secret-medical-et-professionnel-823988.html|title=l'Union des Comores d\u00e9nonce \" Une violation du secret m\u00e9dical et professionnel \"|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, the ARS announced 191 cases, including 41 health professionals; 17 people are hospitalized, including 4 in intensive care; 50 patients are recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-mayotte-191-cas-confirmes-au-total|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 \u00e0 Mayotte : 191 cas confirm\u00e9s au total|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n<br>\nThe report of the Scientific Council on the Evolution of the Coronavirus in the Overseas Territories has been released which calls for strict confinement, doubling of hospital capactity. The situation in Mayotte is considered worrying and therefore calls for an \"extra-hospital\" structure to isolate the asymptomatic cases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/coronavirus-le-conseil-scientifique-craint-une-aggravation-de-la-situation-outre-mer-et-preconise-le-maintien-strict-du-confinement-821800.html|title=Coronavirus: the scientific council fears a worsening of the Overseas situation and recommends \"the strict maintenance of confinement\"|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April, a third death was declared; the number of cases increases slightly to 196.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-mayotte-enregistre-un-3eme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-822004.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte enregistre un 3\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au COVID-19|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April, there are 203 confirmed cases. 67 people have recovered, and more than 1,400 tests have been performed thus far.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-le-cap-des-200-cas-est-franchi-a-mayotte-822244.html |title=Coronavirus : Le cap des 200 cas est franchi \u00e0 Mayotte |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re |language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April, there are 207 confirmed cases including 42 health workers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-covid-19-a-mayotte-207-cas-confirmes-au-total-soit-4-cas-supplementaires-en-24h-822452.html|title=Coronavirus : 207 cas confirm\u00e9s au total, soit 4 cas suppl\u00e9mentaires en 24h. |language=fr|access-date=13 April 2002|website=France TV info}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 April, health care professionals from France have come to the aid of Mayotte. They have all been tested prior to boarding, and will not be quarantined on arrival, but have to abide by special precautionary rules.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-10-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-en-24h-217-au-total-822818.html| title=Coronavirus : 10 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s en 24h, 217 au total| language=fr | access-date=14 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April, a group of students from Mayotte in France, have written open letter that they wished to be repatriated because they have been confined in a near empty [[dormitory]] for almost a month now.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Pour le rapatriement des \u00e9tudiants Mahorais|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/pour-le-rapatriement-des-etudiants-mahorais-823208.html|language=fr | access-date=15 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref> No plans for repatriation from France have been announced yet.\n\nA positive case was discovered from [[Comoros]] where there are officially no Covid-19 infections. As a result, all nautical activities have been banned in order to better guard against illegal border crossings by boat.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/un-cas-de-coronavirus-a-ete-importe-des-comores-823226.html|title=Un cas de Coronavirus a \u00e9t\u00e9 import\u00e9 des Comores|language=fr | access-date=15 April 2020| website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April, measures have been put in place for pregnant women, because up to date 10 tested positive. 1,600 tests have been performed.<ref name=\"upd-04-16\">{{Cite news |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-12-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-a-mayotte-233-au-total-823556.html |title=Coronavirus : 12 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Mayotte, 233 au total |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re| language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n<br>\n[[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Colombet]], the [[List of colonial and departmental heads of Mayotte|Prefect]] of Mayotte, said that the current situation is a fight on multiple fronts where food aid is also a major issue. \u20ac2 million in food stamps are being distributed. Colombet also calls upon the food markets to remain open during [[Ramadan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/le-prefet-de-mayotte-on-y-va-a-fond-823250.html|title=Le pr\u00e9fet de Mayotte : \" on y va \u00e0 fond ! \"|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re| language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, the fourth death was announced. 1,700 tests have been performed up to now.<ref name=\"upd-04-17\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-mayotte-enregistre-un-4eme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-823930.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte enregistre un 4\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au COVID-19|language=fr|access-date=17 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April, it was announced that 108 people had died in March, an increase of 30% compared to 2019. 40% of the deaths are people over 75. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/plus-de-3-morts-par-jour-la-surmortalite-se-confirme-a-mayotte-824348.html|title=Plus de 3 morts par jour : la surmortalit\u00e9 se confirme \u00e0 Mayotte |language=fr |access-date=19 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 April, the Association of Mayotte [[Mayors]] consider that the conditions for reopening of schools are not met, and want more guarantees. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/reouverture-des-ecoles-les-11-mai-l-association-des-maires-de-mayotte-souhaite-avoir-plus-de-garantie-825820.html|title=R\u00e9ouverture des \u00e9coles les 11 mai : l\u2019association des maires de Mayotte souhaite avoir plus de garantie|access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Preventive measures==\n* 15 March 2020 - All schools are closed. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Le-prefet-de-Mayotte-annonce-la-fermeture-des-etablissements-scolaires|title=Coronavirus - COVID19  Le pr\u00e9fet de Mayotte annonce la fermeture des \u00e9tablissements scolaires |access-date=23 April 2020|website=mayotte.gouv.gr|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 15 March 2020 - Social distancing must be observed. All non-essential businesses must close. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Arrete-du-15-mars-2020-portant-diverses-mesures-relatives-de-lutte-contre-la-propagation-du-COVID19|title=Arr\u00eat\u00e9 du 15 mars 2020 portant diverses mesures relatives de lutte contre la propagation du COVID19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 18 March 2020 - People entering Mayotte must self isolate for 14 days. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Un-controle-sanitaire-renforce-a-l-aeroport-de-Dzaoudzi-COVID19|title=Un contr\u00f4le sanitaire renforc\u00e9 \u00e0 l\u2019a\u00e9roport de Dzaoudzi - COVID19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 20 March 2020 - Access to beaches, coves and (uninhabited) islands is prohibited. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Les-plages-criques-et-ilots-de-Mayotte-interdites-d-acces-COVID19|title=Covid19 - Les plages, criques et \u00eelots de Mayotte interdites d\u2019acc\u00e8s |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n* 25 March 2020 - A [[curfew]] was instituted between 20:00 and 05:00. Gathering with more than two people are banned. Traffic restrictions apply throughout the island. <ref name=\"curfew\"/>\n* 22 April 2020 - Farmers' markets are reopened in [[Coconi]], [[Chirongui]], and [[Kaweni]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.gouv.fr/Politiques-publiques/Sante/CORONAVIRUS-COVID-19/Dispositif-mis-en-place/Ouverture-de-marches-de-producteurs-a-Coconi-Chirongui-Kaweni-COVID-19|title=Ouverture de march\u00e9s de producteurs \u00e0 Coconi, Chirongui, Kaweni COVID-19 |access-date=23 April 2020|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\n==Statistics==\nChronology of the number of active cases\n{{Graph:Chart\n| type = line\n| linewidth = 1\n| showSymbols = 1\n| yType= integer\n| width = 600\n| colors = #ff6347, cyan, black\n| xAxisTitle = Date\n| xAxisAngle = -40\n| xType = date\n| xAxisFormat = %e %b\n| x = 12 March 2020, 13 March 2020, 14 March 2020, 15 March 2020, 16 March 2020, 17 March 2020, 18 March 2020 , 19 March 2020, 20 March 2020, 21 March 2020, 22 March 2020, 23 March 2020, 24 March 2020, 25 March 2020, 26 March 2020, 27 March 2020, 28 March 2020, 29 March 2020, 30 March 2020, 31 March 2020,\n1 April 2020, 2 April 2020, 3 April 2020, 4 April 2020, 5 April 2020, 6 April 2020, 7 April 2020, 8 April 2020, 9 April 2020, 10 April 2020, 11 April 2020, 12 April 2020, 13 April 2020, 14 April 2020, 15 April 2020, 16 April 2020, 17 April 2020, 18 April 2020, 19 April 2020, 20 April 2020, 21 April 2020, 22 April 2020, 23 April 2020\n| yAxisTitle = No. of cases\n| y1 = \n0,     1,   1,   1,   1,   1,   3,   3,   4,   6,   9,  11,  21,  30,  35,  42,  46,  56, 66, 72, 83, <!-- March -->\n90,  104, 113, 118, 131, 147, 147, 159, 146, 139, 136, 133, 135, 145, 144, <!-- -15 April -->\n136, 124, 133, 150, 163